{
  "stem": "14251.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we pulled this off the finger of a stranger selling baby buggies in East Berlin in 1948.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He instinctively knew something was peculiar.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he said, you're not here for baby buggies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my mother and I shook our heads and said, no.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he had his hands behind his back to hide them, as if he knew.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my mother said, I'm here for that ring that you're wearing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He took it off.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, it is not mine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I got it during the hard times in the early post-war years, '45, '46.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he readily gave it back because my mother could have called the Russian police, which at that point would have given us the ring.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she gave him money for it, which he did not want.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But she felt-- she's always been a person who is very just about everything.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Gave him money.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The watch was kept by my grandparents' neighbors named Baus, B-A-U-S.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And particularly, Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Baus had been helpful to us during the underground, in hiding, days by supplying us with very expensive, gold-tipped-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what do you call those?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Fountain pens.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, they were valuable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, they are pens that cost, even here, hundreds of dollars.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That kind of quality.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he gave us that to help us, if we sold them, to turn into money for food or whatever.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They kept this and six of-- of my mother's original silverware and a watch that belonged to my mother that their daughter, who had been her girlfriend, although she was not-- they were not Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was unusual to have friends that were not Jewish, but these families were close friends since 1922.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
